Brewed Awakening - Menu Optimization Analysis
A data-driven menu analysis for a campus coffee shop, tasked with reducing a 22-item menu to an optimal 10–12 items. Items were evaluated across four dimensions
[contribution margin, preparation time, demand volume, and demand stability (measured via Coefficient of Variation) ] to identify the highest-value offerings and inform a streamlined, operationally efficient menu.
Built as part of BUSI 414.
Data courtesy of Alym Almani.
